<br>
Eastern Karana has this code (much to my surprise), my bard (albiet a few lvl's ago) would load selo's up and grab every blue hound, lion, crag he could find.  Now he had to be careful to not get hit mind you.  The best example I can say without a doubt (and also the best way to kite them all), is to use 1 particular type so that their run speed will make them group together (whereass, 6 crags run alot slower than 6 hounds wich run slower than 6 lions, which makes a harder kite and a bad example).<br>
<br>
So one pull I actually got 14 hounds (and stalkers but they run the same speed) to give chase to me.  To get them in range for my AoE song to hit them I actually had to be real close (which always resulted in inside) to melee range.  With the way it was coded it was timeable to have all the mobs inside AoE range when the AoE actually hit, but I could ONLY be hit by 3 of the mobs at a time.  This resulted in 2 things happening first some of the mobs would politely wait their turn (right out of melee range) others would bolt (which kinda looked like an exploding star).  So it was selo, AoE, selo to avoid losing the train I worked soo hard to build up (believe me they could barely touch me when they were evens so I could have stood there in one place singing).<br>
<br>
That being said, once in a blue moon a 4th 5th 6th and so on would sometimes stand in melee range attacking in between others attacks.  Does that mean that it's coded for 6 to be able to be beating me at once? NO but it does mean they can/will stand there waiting for their turn.<br>
<br>
